<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="KR6t0288-en-7f7180c9" type="transl"><teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>Shobogenzo</title><editor role="translator">Yokoi</editor></titleStmt><publicationStmt><ab>published electronically as part of the TLS project at https://hxwd.org</ab><availability status="3">This work has not been licensed for use in the TLS</availability></publicationStmt><sourceDesc><bibl><title>Shobogenzo</title>Sankibo, Tokyo, 1986</bibl><ab>Translation of <bibl corresp="#KR6t0288"><title xml:lang="och">正法眼藏</title></bibl> into <lang xml:lang="en">English</lang>.</ab></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><creation resp="#chris">Initially created: <date>2024-03-14T09:48:08.83+09:00</date> by chris</creation></profileDesc></teiHeader><text><body><div><head>Translated parts</head><p xml:id="KR6t0288-start"><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b09-h.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:16:08.561+09:00">Uji (Being-Time, or the Identity of Being and Time)</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s1" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T09:53:12.76+09:00">A high monk1 once said:</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s2" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T09:53:16.954+09:00">"The uji is standing on the top of a mountain,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s3" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T09:53:19.693+09:00">going to the bottom of the deep sea;</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s4" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T09:53:21.71+09:00">[Acala2 with] three heads and eight arms,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s5" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T09:53:24.015+09:00">[the Buddha-body of] eight3 or sixteen feet4;</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s6" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T09:53:28.729+09:00">a shujō5 and a hossu6,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s7" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T09:53:30.436+09:00">a round pillar and a garden lantern,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s8" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T09:53:33.785+09:00">ordinary people;</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s9" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T09:53:36.243+09:00">and the earth and the sky"</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s9a" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T09:54:02.97+09:00">The "uji"</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s10" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T09:54:03.879+09:00">means that time is being</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s11" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:10:43.597+09:00">and vice versa.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s12" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:10:45.667+09:00">The Buddha-body of sixteen feet is time.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s14" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:10:49.415+09:00">it has a glorious function of time.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s15" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:10:52.161+09:00">About this we must study the twenty-four hours of today.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s13" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:10:47.327+09:00">Therefore,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s16" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:15:44.998+09:00">[Acala with] three heads and eight arms is also time.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s17" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:16:16.352+09:00">Therefore,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s18" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:16:21.159+09:00">he is identical with the twenty-four hours of today.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s19" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:16:37.429+09:00">Indeed we have never measured the length of the hours,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s20" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:16:38.272+09:00">but we call them such.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s21" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:17:03.707+09:00">...</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s22" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:17:35.693+09:00">The passing traces [of things] are so clear</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s23" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:17:37.245+09:00">that no one has ever doubted them.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s24" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:17:53.977+09:00">However,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s25" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:17:54.867+09:00">this does not mean that they know them well.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s26" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:18:43.408+09:00">Originally, ordinary people</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s27" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:18:50.457+09:00">did not always doubt unknown things or matters,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s28" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:33:20.38+09:00">so their future doubt</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s29" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:33:21.307+09:00">is not always consistent</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s30" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:33:24.346+09:00">with their present one.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s31" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:33:37.964+09:00">[For this reason] doubt itself</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s32" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:33:38.993+09:00">is only a provisional aspect of time.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s33" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:42:20.543+09:00">We regard ourselves as the whole universe.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s34" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:42:29.099+09:00">Therefore, we should regard each thing in whole world</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s35" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:42:29.879+09:00">as its provisional aspect of time.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s36" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:42:45.82+09:00">Each thing does not  hinder others</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s37" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:42:46.572+09:00">any more than each time does.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s38" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:43:05.185+09:00">Therefore,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s39" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:44:12.257+09:00">we are awakened to the bodhi-mind,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s40" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:44:15.047+09:00">train ourselves and</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s41" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:44:18.301+09:00">become enlightened,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s42" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:45:08.725+09:00">identically and simultaneously</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s43" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:45:09.725+09:00">with the whole universe.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s44" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:45:56.523+09:00">In short, we regard  ourselves as such.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s45" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:45:57.398+09:00">Such is the fact that we ourselves</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s46" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:45:58.514+09:00">are time.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s47" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:59:22.458+09:00">For this reason,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s48" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:59:33.573+09:00">we must realize that there are various things in the whole world</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s49" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T10:59:55.353+09:00">and that each of them is in [identical with] the whole world.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s50" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:00:26.269+09:00">To realize this one-whole</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s51" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:00:26.957+09:00">is the starting point of Buddhist training.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s52" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:00:35.695+09:00">As soon as we have reached this realm,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s53" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:01:24.082+09:00">we shall find that each thing is always such</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s54" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:01:25.276+09:00">whether we can understand it or not.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s55" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:01:28.015+09:00"/><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s56" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:01:36.382+09:00">Therefore,each time is the whole.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s57" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:01:52.98+09:00">All things and phenomena are time.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s58" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:03:36.646+09:00"/><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s59" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:03:57.547+09:00">Each time</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s60" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:04:01.948+09:00">is the whole being and the world.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s61" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:04:23.446+09:00">Let us just try to see or think</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0045b10.s62" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:04:24.519+09:00">if there is the whole being or the world apart from the present time.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c11-h.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:06:16.649+09:00">Sansui-kyo (Mountains and Water in Buddhism)</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s1" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:11:39.16+09:00">Mountains and water [before us] now</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s2" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:11:40.38+09:00">are the appearance of the Law of ancient high monks.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s3" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:13:01.905+09:00">Mountains are nothing but mountains;</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s4" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:13:02.768+09:00">water is nothing but water</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s5" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:13:11.014+09:00">From time immemorial both of them are ultimate reality,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s6" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:13:16.445+09:00">so they have their own free function now;</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s7" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:13:43.038+09:00">they are also original,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s8" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:13:49.877+09:00">and so are beyond actuality.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s9" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:14:20.033+09:00">A mountain has great functions</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s10" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:14:25.273+09:00">[that give rise to clouds or the wind].</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s11" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:14:47.069+09:00">By studying this we never fail</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s12" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:14:48.101+09:00">to realize the free function</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s13" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:14:50.151+09:00">of going on clouds and with the wind.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s13.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:20:18.258+09:00">Abbot Tao-kai1 of Mount Ta-yang said to some monks,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s14" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:20:19.912+09:00">"A blue mountain always walks.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s15" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:20:21.089+09:00">A sterile maiden has a baby at night."</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s16" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:21:17.608+09:00">A mountain has its own function fully.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s17" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:21:18.673+09:00">...</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s18" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:21:20.714+09:00">Therefore it is always stable</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s19" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:21:21.987+09:00">and walks.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s20" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:21:38.195+09:00">We must study</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s21" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:21:38.603+09:00">this walk carefully.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s22" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:22:06.158+09:00">Ordinarily, we may think it walks</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s23" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:22:07.443+09:00">like a man's,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s24" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:22:09.021+09:00">but we must not doubt this only</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s25" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:22:11.88+09:00">because it does not look so.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s26" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:22:33.926+09:00">His statement</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s27" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:22:38.948+09:00">already shows us that [a mountain] walks.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s28" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:23:26.511+09:00">This is the essence of the walk of the mountain.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s29" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:23:34.611+09:00">We must clarify his words "...always walks"</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s30" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:23:56.893+09:00">A mountain walks, so it is always stable.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s31" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:24:33.269+09:00">It walks much faster</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s32" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:24:34.344+09:00">than the wind,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s33" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:24:36.71+09:00">but a man on the mountain</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s34" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:24:39.701+09:00">is ignorant [of this fact].</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s35" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:27:47.426+09:00">Because a mountain is [nothing but a mountain]</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s36" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:27:47.988+09:00">just as when blossoms open the whole world becomes spring-like.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s37" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:28:34.394+09:00">The same can also be said</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s38" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:28:35.698+09:00">of a man outside the mountain.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s39" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:29:03.546+09:00">[Because his world is nothing but his world.]  For this reason, those who have no eye for this mountain</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s40" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:29:11.832+09:00">cannot realize, know,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s41" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:29:12.72+09:00">see or hear this fact.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s42" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:32:29.505+09:00">Those who doubt the walk of a mountain</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s43" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:32:39.499+09:00">would be unaware of, and blind to, their own walk,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s44" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:32:42.07+09:00">though really they walk themselves.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s45" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:33:23.963+09:00"/><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s46" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:34:13.79+09:00"/><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s48" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:34:15.458+09:00">On the contrary, however, those who realize their own walk</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s49" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:34:10.928+09:00">will unfailingly grasp that of a blue mountain.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s50" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:34:59.657+09:00">The blue mountain is no more sentient</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s51" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:35:00.731+09:00">or insentient being</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s52" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:35:02.516+09:00">than ourselves.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s53" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:35:27.34+09:00"/><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s54" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:35:58.486+09:00">Now we cannot doubt the walk of a blue mountain,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s55" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:35:59.356+09:00">nor can we tell how fare it walks.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s56" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:38:15.053+09:00">We should carefully examine various kinds of walk</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s57" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:38:16.294+09:00">- the constantly free advance and retreat from time immemorial -</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s58" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:38:36.126+09:00">of a blue mountain and of our own.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s66" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:42:26.985+09:00">If the various kinds of walk stop,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s67" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:42:32.652+09:00">no Buddhas and patriarchs will appear in the world.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s68" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:42:41.83+09:00">If they had come to an end,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s69" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:42:42.458+09:00">the Law would not be transmitted now.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s70" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:43:04.794+09:00">[A blue mountain] is always going ahead</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s71" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:43:05.88+09:00">and back.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s72" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:43:26.595+09:00">But its going-ahead</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s73" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:43:27.283+09:00">is not for or against its going-back,</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s74" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:43:33.707+09:00">and vice versa.</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s75" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:43:39.525+09:00"/><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s76" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:43:55.09+09:00">We regard this function as the flowing of a mountain</seg><seg corresp="#KR6t0288_T_82-2582.0062c12.s77" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2024-03-14T11:43:56.146+09:00">or a flowing mountain.</seg></p></div></body></text></TEI>